title: Tycho
comment: Reverted [[WP:AGF|good faith]] edits by [[Special:Contributions/Captain bookworm|Captain bookworm]] ([[User talk:Captain bookworm|talk]]): Might want to read [[MOS:DABONE]] and [[MOS:DABOTHERLANG]]
text:
'''Tycho''' is a masculine given name, a latinization of Greek Τύχων, from the name of  [[Tyche]] ({{lang-grc-gre|Τύχη|link=no}}), the Greek goddess of fortune or luck.
The Russian form of the name is ''[[Tikhon]]'' (Тихон).

{{tocright}}

==People==
Given name
* [[Tycho Brahe]] (1546–1601), Danish nobleman and astronomer
* Saint [[Tikhon of Zadonsk]] (1724–1783), Russian bishop
* [[Tycho van Meer]] (born 1974), Dutch field hockey striker
Surname
* [[Tommy Tycho]] (1928–2013), Hungarian-Australian pianist, conductor, composer
Pseudonym
* [[Tycho (musician)]] (born 1977) (Scott Hansen), American ambient music artist and producer, also known as ISO50

==Astronomy==
* [[Tycho (lunar crater)]]
* [[Tycho Brahe (Martian crater)]]
* The [[Hipparcos Catalogue|Tycho-1 Catalogue]] or [[Tycho-2 Catalogue]] of stars
* [[SN 1572]], a supernova remnant, often called Tycho's supernova
* [[Tycho G]], the companion star of SN 1572
* [[1677 Tycho Brahe]], an asteroid

==Fiction==
* Tycho, a desert ranger henchman from the computer game [[Fallout (video game)|''Fallout'']]
* Tycho, a shipboard AI in the computer game [[Marathon (video game)|''Marathon'']]
* Tycho Brahe, a character from the [[Penny Arcade|''Penny Arcade'' webcomic]] based on writer Jerry Holkins
* Tycho Celchu, a character in the ''[[Star Wars]]'' Universe
* Brother-Captain Tycho, a character in the ''[[Warhammer 40,000]]'' universe
* Tycho City, a city located on Earth's moon (presumably on/near Tycho Crater), mentioned in the ''[[Star Trek]]'' franchise
* Tycho Station, a setting in ''[[The Expanse (novel series)|The Expanse]]'' novel series and its accompanying TV series
